e":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From a Late Latin personal name, which was borne by a saint martyred in Rome, together with Saints Faustinus and Simplicius, in the early 4th century. The original form of the name was probably <i>Viatrix</i>, a feminine version of <i>Viator</i> ‘voyager (through life)’, which was a favourite name among early Christians. This was then altered by association with Latin <i>Beatus</i> ‘blessed’ (<i>Via-</i> and <i>Bea-</i> sometimes being pronounced the same in Late Latin).  See also  Beatrice ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Beatrix Broye was born in 1270, in Glamorgan, Wales, United Kingdom, her father, John Broye, was 26 and her mother, Jeanne de Sains, was 23. She had at least 3 sons with John Porter I. She died in 1345, in her hometown, at the age of 75."},"et":{"1270–1345":"1270–1345","1267–1316":"1267–1316","1285–Male":"1285–Surnud","1292–1329":"1292–1329","1294–1348":"1294–1348","1245–Male":"1245–Surnud","1248–Female":"1248–Surnud","about 1294":"umbes 1294","1285":"1285","14 May 1329":"14. mai 1329","1294":"1294","1270":"1270","1292":"1292","1316":"1316","1348":"1348","1248":"1248","1345":"1345","1245":"1245","1267":"1267","about 1265":"umbes 1265","1329":"1329","11 June 1292":"11. juuni 1292","Surrey, England":"Surrey, England","Bletsoe, Bedfordshire, England":"Bletsoe, Bedfordshire, England","Fonmon Castle, Vale of Galmorgan, Wales":"Ffwl-y-Mwn, Glamorgan, Wales","Fonmon Castle, Glamorganshire, Wales":"Ffwl-y-Mwn, Glamorgan, Wales","Bosing, Hampshire, England":"Hampshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Faumont Castle, Glamorgan, Wales":"Glamorgan, Wales, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1270–1345":"1270–1345","1267–1316":"1267–1316","1285–Male":"1285–Kuollut","1292–1329":"1292–1329","1294–1348":"1294–1348","1245–Male":"1245–Kuollut","1248–Female":"1248–Kuollut","about 1294":"noin 1294","1285":"1285","14 May 1329":"14. toukokuuta 1329","1294":"1294"